# Observability Conventions

## Prometheus Metrics

### Naming
- `snake_case` only
- Format: `<domain>_<action>_<unit>` — e.g. `scenario_runs_total`, `scenario_run_duration_seconds`
- Counters end in `_total`
- Histograms end in `_seconds` or `_bytes`

### Required labels
- Counters: always include `type` and `status`
- Histograms: always include `type`

### Where to add
- Inject `MetricsService` via constructor
- Increment in service layer, not controller
- Always observe histogram at end of operation

```typescript
// Counter example
this.metrics.scenarioRunsTotal.inc({ type: dto.type, status: 'completed' });

// Histogram example
this.metrics.scenarioRunDuration.observe({ type: dto.type }, durationSeconds);
```

## Structured Logging (Loki)

Use `Logger` from `@nestjs/common`. nestjs-pino outputs JSON automatically.

### Every log MUST include
```typescript
this.logger.log({
  message: 'Human-readable description',
  scenarioType: dto.type,      // for Loki filtering
  scenarioId: run.id,
  duration: ms,
  // + error: string if applicable
});
```

### Log levels
- `log()` / `info` — normal operations
- `warn()` — slow requests, validation errors, degraded state
- `error()` — exceptions, failed operations

## Sentry

- Call `Sentry.captureException(exception)` for all 5xx errors (already in GlobalExceptionFilter)
- Call `Sentry.addBreadcrumb()` for warning-level scenarios
- DSN configured via `SENTRY_DSN` env variable
- Do NOT add Sentry calls in controllers — use the filter + explicit service calls
